iclocalization.add_attachments_for_ie_browser:
The Internet Explorer settings prohibit attachments for CA Service Catalog. To allow these attachments, follow these steps:

 1.  Click Tools, Internet Options, and click the Security tab.
 2. Select Local Intranet and click Custom Level.
 3.  For the "Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting" setting, click Enable, and click OK. You return to the Security tab.
 4.  Select Trusted Sites and click Sites.
 5.  Add the URL for accessing CA Service Catalog (for example, http://hostname:8080 or https://hostname:8080 ) to the trusted sites, and click Close. Close the Internet Options dialog.
 6. Log out of CA Service Catalog, and restart Internet Explorer.
 7.  Log in to CA Service Catalog again, and verify that you can add attachments.
